WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.240 --> 00:00:10.040
Ooh! Careful. Homer!

2
00:00:10.160 --> 00:00:12.440
There's no time. We're late.

3
00:00:14.760 --> 00:00:16.960
O little town of Bethlehem

4
00:00:16.960 --> 00:00:18.200
O little town of Bethlehem

5
00:00:18.280 --> 00:00:22.800
How still we see the elie

6
00:00:22.920 --> 00:00:25.480
-Excuse me. Pardon me.

7
00:00:25.600 --> 00:00:27.400
- Sorry. Excuse me.
- Hey. Norman. how's it goin'?

8
00:00:27.520 --> 00:00:29.320
So you got dragged down here
too. huh?

9
00:00:29.440 --> 00:00:31.240
- How you doin'. Fred?
- Sorry. Excuse me.

10
00:00:31.360 --> 00:00:33.160
- Yeah. 'Scuse me. Oh!

11
00:00:33.240 --> 00:00:36.320
Pardon my galoshes.

12
00:00:36.320 --> 00:00:40.720
Are met in thee tonight

13
00:00:42.840 --> 00:00:45.160
Wasn't that wonderful?

14
00:00:45.160 --> 00:00:49.160
And now
"Santas of many lands."

15
00:00:49.280 --> 00:00:52.640
as presented by the entire
second grade class.

16
00:00:52.720 --> 00:00:55.120
Oh! Lisa's class.

17
00:00:55.240 --> 00:00:57.440
Frohliche Weihnachten.

18
00:00:57.520 --> 00:00:59.920
That's German for
" Merry Christmas."

19
00:00:59.920 --> 00:01:05.200
In Germany. Santa's servant Ruprecht
gives presents to good children...

20
00:01:05.280 --> 00:01:08.360
and whipping rods
to the parents of bad ones.

21
00:01:11.640 --> 00:01:13.440
Merry Kurisumasu.

22
00:01:13.520 --> 00:01:18.640
I am Hotseiosha. a japanese priest
who acts like Santa Claus.

23
00:01:18.720 --> 00:01:21.120
I have eyes
in the back ofmy head...

24
00:01:21.200 --> 00:01:24.360
so children better behave
when I'm nearby.

25
00:01:26.400 --> 00:01:29.440
Now presenting Lisa Simpson...

26
00:01:29.560 --> 00:01:34.640
as Tawanga. the Santa Claus
of the South Seas.

27
00:01:34.720 --> 00:01:36.560
Ooh. it's Lisa! That's ours.

28
00:01:50.080 --> 00:01:54.120
Ah. the fourth grade
will now favor us with a melody--

29
00:01:54.200 --> 00:01:57.640
Uh. medley
of holiday "flavorites."

30
00:01:57.760 --> 00:02:00.160
Dashing through the snow

31
00:02:00.240 --> 00:02:02.560
In a one-horse open sleigh

32
00:02:02.640 --> 00:02:04.480
O'er the fields we go

33
00:02:04.560 --> 00:02:06.560
Laughing all the way
Ha ha ha

34
00:02:06.680 --> 00:02:08.680
Bells on bobtail ring

35
00:02:08.800 --> 00:02:11.840
- Isn't Bart sweet. Homer?

36
00:02:11.960 --> 00:02:15.000
He sings like an angel.

37
00:02:15.120 --> 00:02:18.360
Oh. jingle bells
Batman smells

38
00:02:18.480 --> 00:02:20.280
Robin laid an egg

39
00:02:20.400 --> 00:02:22.400
The Batmobile
broke its wheel

40
00:02:22.480 --> 00:02:24.600
The joker got awa--

41
00:02:24.600 --> 00:02:26.720
Jingle bells
Jingle bells

42
00:02:26.800 --> 00:02:28.640
Jingle all

43
00:02:28.720 --> 00:02:30.840
The fifth grade will now favour us...

44
00:02:30.840 --> 00:02:35.720
with a scene from Charles. uh. Dickens'
A Christmas Carol.

45
00:02:35.840 --> 00:02:40.160
How many grades does this school have?

46
00:02:40.240 --> 00:02:43.680
" Dear friends of the Simpson family.

47
00:02:43.800 --> 00:02:46.840
"We had some sadness and
some gladness this year.

48
00:02:46.960 --> 00:02:49.240
" First. the sadness.
Our little cat Snowball...

49
00:02:49.360 --> 00:02:52.320
"was unexpectedly run over
and went to kitty heaven.

50
00:02:52.400 --> 00:02:54.920
"But we bought
a new little cat. Snowball I.

51
00:02:55.000 --> 00:02:57.600
"So I guess life goes on.

52
00:02:57.680 --> 00:03:02.200
"Speaking of life going on.
Grandpa's still with us. feisty as ever.

53
00:03:02.280 --> 00:03:04.120
" Maggie is walking by herself.

54
00:03:04.200 --> 00:03:07.680
"Lisa got straight A's.
and Bart--

55
00:03:07.760 --> 00:03:10.080
"Well. we love Bart.

56
00:03:10.160 --> 00:03:12.960
"The magic of the season
has touched us all.

57
00:03:13.040 --> 00:03:15.160
Marge. haven't you finished
that stupid letter yet?

58
00:03:15.160 --> 00:03:18.320
- " Homer sends his love. Happy holidays.
- Marge!

59
00:03:18.400 --> 00:03:20.600
- The Simpsons."
- Marge. where's the extension cord?

60
00:03:20.720 --> 00:03:23.400
For heaven's sake. Homer.
It's in the utility drawer.

61
00:03:23.480 --> 00:03:25.800
Sorry. I'm just a big kid.

62
00:03:25.880 --> 00:03:28.080
And I love Christmas
so much.

63
00:03:29.160 --> 00:03:32.040
D'oh!

64
00:03:32.120 --> 00:03:34.120
All right. children.
let me have those letters.

65
00:03:34.240 --> 00:03:36.920
I'll send them to Santa's workshop
at the North Pole.

66
00:03:36.920 --> 00:03:38.920
Oh. please. There's only
one fat guy that brings us presents.

67
00:03:38.920 --> 00:03:40.840
and his name ain't Santa.

68
00:03:40.840 --> 00:03:44.000
Uh-- A pony?

69
00:03:44.120 --> 00:03:47.560
Oh. Lisa. you've asked for that
for the last three years.

70
00:03:47.640 --> 00:03:51.000
and I keep telling you Santa can't
fit a pony into his sleigh.

71
00:03:51.120 --> 00:03:52.920
Can't you take a hint?

72
00:03:53.040 --> 00:03:54.840
But I really want a pony.

73
00:03:54.960 --> 00:03:58.000
- and I've been really good this year.
- Oh. dear.

74
00:03:58.120 --> 00:04:00.720
Maybe Bart is
a little more realistic.

75
00:04:00.800 --> 00:04:02.600
- A tattoo?
- A what?

76
00:04:02.720 --> 00:04:04.920
Yeah! They're cool. and they last
the rest of your life.

77
00:04:04.920 --> 00:04:07.600
you will not be getting
a tattoo for Christmas.

78
00:04:07.720 --> 00:04:10.760
Yeah. If you want one. you'll have
to pay for it out of your allowance.

79
00:04:10.880 --> 00:04:12.200
- All right!
- Homer!

80
00:04:12.200 --> 00:04:14.120
- "Yello."

81
00:04:14.120 --> 00:04:16.040
- Marge. please.
- Who's this?

82
00:04:16.160 --> 00:04:17.960
May I please speak to Marge?

83
00:04:18.040 --> 00:04:20.760
- This is her sister. isn't it?
- Is Marge there?

84
00:04:20.840 --> 00:04:24.120
- Who shall I say is calling?
- Marge. please.

85
00:04:24.120 --> 00:04:27.280
It's your sister.
Oh!

86
00:04:27.360 --> 00:04:29.760
- Hello.
- Hello. Marge. It's Patty.

87
00:04:29.840 --> 00:04:34.160
Selma and I couldn't be more excited
about seeing our sister Christmas Eve.

88
00:04:34.280 --> 00:04:38.120
Well. Homer and I are looking
forward to your visit too.

89
00:04:40.040 --> 00:04:42.400
Somehow I doubt
that Homer is excited.

90
00:04:42.520 --> 00:04:44.320
of all the men
you could've married.

91
00:04:44.440 --> 00:04:47.200
I don't know why you picked
one who's always so rude to us.

92
00:04:47.320 --> 00:04:49.520
- Good one. Dad.

93
00:04:49.600 --> 00:04:52.200
Okay. kids.
prepare to be dazzled.

94
00:04:52.280 --> 00:04:54.880
Marge. turn on the juice!

95
00:04:57.280 --> 00:04:59.600
- What do you think. kids?

96
00:04:59.680 --> 00:05:01.520
- Nice try. Dad.

97
00:05:01.600 --> 00:05:03.720
Just hold
your horses. son. Hey. Simpson!

98
00:05:03.800 --> 00:05:07.440
- What is it. Flanders?
- Do you think this looks okay?

99
00:05:07.440 --> 00:05:11.080
Ho ho ho. Ho ho ho.

100
00:05:11.200 --> 00:05:12.520
- Oh!
- Oh. neato!

101
00:05:12.640 --> 00:05:14.920
It's too bright.

102
00:05:15.040 --> 00:05:17.240
I oughta-- Flanders.
What a big show-off.

103
00:05:20.400 --> 00:05:22.600
- Kids. wanna go Christmas shopping?
- I do!

104
00:05:22.680 --> 00:05:25.080
- All right! The mall!
- Go get your money.

105
00:05:25.200 --> 00:05:28.280
Tell us. Marge. Where have
you been hiding the Christmas money?

106
00:05:28.360 --> 00:05:30.960
Oh. I have my secrets.

107
00:05:31.040 --> 00:05:32.960
Turn around.

108
00:05:35.840 --> 00:05:39.280
- you can look now.
- Ooh! Big jar this year.

109
00:05:58.080 --> 00:06:00.000
Oh. Bart.
that's so sweet.

110
00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:02.400
It's the best present
a mother could get.

111
00:06:02.520 --> 00:06:04.880
and it makes you look
so dangerous.

112
00:06:07.480 --> 00:06:09.520
- One " Mother." please.

113
00:06:09.600 --> 00:06:11.400
Wait a minute.
How old are you?

114
00:06:11.520 --> 00:06:13.440
- Twenty-one. sir.
- Get in the chair.

115
00:06:19.480 --> 00:06:21.280
Mm-hmm.

116
00:06:21.400 --> 00:06:24.160
Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

117
00:06:24.280 --> 00:06:27.040
- Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

118
00:06:27.160 --> 00:06:29.640
Attention.
all personnel. please keep working...

119
00:06:29.720 --> 00:06:31.560
during the following
announcement.

120
00:06:31.640 --> 00:06:35.000
And now our boss and friend
Mr. Burns.

121
00:06:35.120 --> 00:06:37.320
Hello. I'm proud to announce...

122
00:06:37.400 --> 00:06:40.200
that we've been able to increase
safety here at the plant...

123
00:06:40.280 --> 00:06:42.400
without increasing the cost
to the consumer...

124
00:06:42.480 --> 00:06:44.600
or affecting management
payraises.

125
00:06:44.600 --> 00:06:47.560
However. for you
semiskilled workers.

126
00:06:47.560 --> 00:06:49.480
there will be
no Christmas bonuses.

127
00:06:49.480 --> 00:06:52.960
- Oh. and one more thing.

128
00:06:53.040 --> 00:06:54.880
Merry Christmas!

129
00:06:54.960 --> 00:06:58.320
- Oh. thank God for the big jar.

130
00:07:00.520 --> 00:07:03.400
- Where's that Bart?

131
00:07:09.240 --> 00:07:13.080
But. Mom.
I thought you'd like it.

132
00:07:14.800 --> 00:07:17.480
Yes. Mrs. Simpson. we can remove
your son's tattoo.

133
00:07:17.600 --> 00:07:19.880
It's a simple routine
involving lasers.

134
00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:22.200
- Cool!
- However. it is rather expensive.

135
00:07:22.200 --> 00:07:24.880
and we must insist
on a cash payment up front.

136
00:07:24.960 --> 00:07:27.000
- Cash?
- Mm-hmm.

137
00:07:27.000 --> 00:07:29.880
Thank God for
Homer's Christmas bonus.

138
00:07:31.600 --> 00:07:35.040
- Ay. caramba!
- Now. whatever you do. don't squirm.

139
00:07:35.160 --> 00:07:39.000
you don't wanna get this sucker
near your eye or your groin.

140
00:07:41.000 --> 00:07:44.440
- Ow! Quit it.

141
00:07:44.560 --> 00:07:46.360
Ow! Quit it.

142
00:07:46.480 --> 00:07:48.280
Ow! Quit it.

143
00:07:48.360 --> 00:07:50.680
- Ow! Quit it.
- Hey. what's with this?

144
00:07:50.680 --> 00:07:54.320
Ow! Quit it!
Used to be a real boss tattoo.

145
00:07:54.440 --> 00:07:57.600
Mom had to spend the Christmas money
having it surgically removed.

146
00:07:57.680 --> 00:08:00.280
Huh?

147
00:08:01.320 --> 00:08:04.200
It's true!

148
00:08:04.280 --> 00:08:07.840
The jar is empty!
Oh. my God!

149
00:08:07.840 --> 00:08:10.160
We're ruined.
Christmas is canceled.

150
00:08:10.240 --> 00:08:12.240
No presents for anyone!

151
00:08:12.360 --> 00:08:15.920
Don't worry. Homer. We'll just
have to stretch your Christmas bonus...

152
00:08:15.920 --> 00:08:18.200
- even further this year.

153
00:08:18.200 --> 00:08:21.280
- Homer?
- Oh. yeah. My Christmas bonus.

154
00:08:21.360 --> 00:08:23.960
How silly of me.

155
00:08:24.040 --> 00:08:26.920
This'll be the best
Christmas yet.

156
00:08:26.920 --> 00:08:28.840
The best any family
ever had.

157
00:08:32.400 --> 00:08:34.320
Hohoho.

158
00:08:35.360 --> 00:08:37.400
Hohoho.

159
00:08:38.520 --> 00:08:41.040
Hohoho.

160
00:08:42.280 --> 00:08:45.360
Ho ho ho.

161
00:08:45.440 --> 00:08:47.280
Hohoho.

162
00:08:49.960 --> 00:08:53.320
Hmm. I get the feeling there's
something you haven't told me. Homer.

163
00:08:53.400 --> 00:08:56.960
- Huh? Oh. I love you. Marge.
- you tell me that all the time.

164
00:08:56.960 --> 00:08:59.080
Oh. good.
because I do love you.

165
00:08:59.160 --> 00:09:02.120
I don't deserve you as much
as a guy with a fat wallet...

166
00:09:02.120 --> 00:09:04.920
and a credit card that won't
set off that horrible beeping.

167
00:09:05.000 --> 00:09:08.080
I think it does have something
to do with your Christmas bonus.

168
00:09:08.160 --> 00:09:10.000
I keep asking for it.
but--

169
00:09:10.080 --> 00:09:13.440
Marge. um.
let me be honest with you.

170
00:09:13.560 --> 00:09:17.560
- Yes?
- Well. I would--

171
00:09:21.120 --> 00:09:23.720
I-- I wanna do
the Christmas shopping this year.

172
00:09:23.720 --> 00:09:26.280
Uh. sure. okay.

173
00:09:29.960 --> 00:09:33.120
Marge. Marge. Hmm. Let'ssee.

174
00:09:33.200 --> 00:09:35.320
Ooh. look!

175
00:09:35.400 --> 00:09:38.680
Pantyhose.
Practical and alluring.

176
00:09:38.760 --> 00:09:41.920
A six-pack.
Oh! Only 4.99.

177
00:09:41.920 --> 00:09:44.040
Ooh! Pads of paper.

178
00:09:44.120 --> 00:09:47.200
I bet Bart can think of
a million things to do with these.

179
00:09:47.320 --> 00:09:50.560
That just leaves
little Maggie. Oh. look!

180
00:09:50.640 --> 00:09:52.560
A little squeak toy.

181
00:09:52.560 --> 00:09:55.440
It says it's for dogs.
but she can't read.

182
00:09:56.400 --> 00:09:59.400
Ow! Oh. Simpson.
it's you.

183
00:09:59.480 --> 00:10:02.920
- Hello. Flanders.
- Oh. my! What a mess we've got here.

184
00:10:03.040 --> 00:10:05.320
Well. which ones are yours
and which ones are mine?

185
00:10:05.320 --> 00:10:08.480
- Well. let's see.
- Oh. this one's mine. This one's mine.

186
00:10:08.600 --> 00:10:11.000
- This one's mine. and this--
- They're all yours!

187
00:10:11.000 --> 00:10:14.040
- Hey. you dropped your pork chop.

188
00:10:14.160 --> 00:10:17.600
- Gimme that!
- Well. happy holidays. Simpson.

189
00:10:17.720 --> 00:10:22.000
- Gee. this is the best Christmas ever.
- You bet.

190
00:10:31.120 --> 00:10:35.080
What's the matter. Homer? Somebody
leave a lump of coal in your stocking?

191
00:10:35.160 --> 00:10:37.280
You've been sitting there.
sucking on a beer all day long.

192
00:10:37.360 --> 00:10:39.560
- So?
- So. it's Christmas.

193
00:10:39.680 --> 00:10:43.200
- Thanks. Moe.

194
00:10:43.320 --> 00:10:45.120
Drinks all around!

195
00:10:45.240 --> 00:10:47.040
What's with
the crazy getup. Barn?

196
00:10:47.160 --> 00:10:51.480
I got me a part-timejob
working as a Santa down at the mall.

197
00:10:51.480 --> 00:10:53.360
Wow! Can I do that?

198
00:10:53.360 --> 00:10:56.160
I don't know. They're
pretty selective.

199
00:10:56.240 --> 00:10:58.080
Do you like children?

200
00:10:58.160 --> 00:11:01.320
What do you mean? All the time?
Even when they're nuts?

201
00:11:01.440 --> 00:11:04.800
- Hmm.
- Uh. I certainly do.

202
00:11:04.880 --> 00:11:06.720
Welcome aboard. Simpson.

203
00:11:06.800 --> 00:11:09.320
Pending your successful completion
of our training program. that is.

204
00:11:09.320 --> 00:11:12.480
Ho ho ho. Ho ho ho.

205
00:11:12.560 --> 00:11:15.360
Ho ho ho. Ho ho ho.

206
00:11:15.360 --> 00:11:18.400
- What is it now. Simpson?
- Uh. when do we get paid?

207
00:11:18.520 --> 00:11:21.880
Not a dime till Christmas Eve!
Now. from the top.

208
00:11:21.960 --> 00:11:25.680
Ho ho ho. Ho ho ho.

209
00:11:25.800 --> 00:11:28.560
Um. Dasher.

210
00:11:28.680 --> 00:11:31.160
- Dancer.
- Mm-hmm.

211
00:11:31.160 --> 00:11:33.280
- Prancer.
- Mm-hmm.

212
00:11:33.360 --> 00:11:35.200
Nixon.

213
00:11:35.280 --> 00:11:38.440
Comet and... Cupid.

214
00:11:38.560 --> 00:11:40.360
- Donna Dixon?
- Sit down. Simpson.

215
00:11:40.480 --> 00:11:42.280
And what would you like.
little boy?

216
00:11:42.400 --> 00:11:44.680
- You're not really Santa. tubby.
- Why. you little egghead!

217
00:11:44.680 --> 00:11:47.280
No. Homer! If such
an emergency arises.

218
00:11:47.280 --> 00:11:50.040
you just tell them
Santa's vey busy this time of year.

219
00:11:50.040 --> 00:11:53.600
- and you are one of his helpers.
- Oh. I knew that one too!

220
00:11:56.480 --> 00:11:58.880
Homer. why are you
seven hours late?

221
00:11:58.960 --> 00:12:01.760
Not a word. Marge.
I'm heading straight for the tub.

222
00:12:01.760 --> 00:12:03.680
But. Homer.
my sisters are here.

223
00:12:03.680 --> 00:12:05.800
- Don't you wanna say hello?

224
00:12:08.080 --> 00:12:10.760
- Daddy! We're so glad to see you!
- Oh. Dad. you're finally home!

225
00:12:10.880 --> 00:12:14.120
What? Why?
Oh. yeah.

226
00:12:14.240 --> 00:12:16.720
Hello. Patty.
Hello. Selma.

227
00:12:16.800 --> 00:12:19.040
- How was your trip?
- Fine.

228
00:12:19.120 --> 00:12:21.240
- you both look well.
- Thank you.

229
00:12:21.320 --> 00:12:24.400
- Yeah. well. Merry Christmas.
- It's Christmas?

230
00:12:24.400 --> 00:12:27.160
- you wouldn't know it around here.
- And why is that?

231
00:12:27.280 --> 00:12:31.120
- For one thing. there's no tree
- I was just on my way out to get one!

232
00:12:31.200 --> 00:12:32.840
- Can we go too. Dad?
- Yeah. can we?

233
00:12:32.920 --> 00:12:34.080
No!

234
00:12:34.160 --> 00:12:36.680
Sleighbells ring

235
00:12:36.680 --> 00:12:39.160
Are you listening

236
00:12:39.160 --> 00:12:41.840
In the lane

237
00:12:41.840 --> 00:12:44.360
Snow is glistening

238
00:12:44.360 --> 00:12:47.600
A beautiful sight

239
00:12:47.600 --> 00:12:50.480
We're happy tonight

240
00:12:50.480 --> 00:12:53.920
- Walking in a winter wonderland

241
00:12:56.440 --> 00:12:58.640
Hey! What do you think you're doin'?

242
00:12:58.720 --> 00:13:00.560
- Uh-oh.
- Hey! Hey!

243
00:13:00.640 --> 00:13:02.640
- Come back here!

244
00:13:05.240 --> 00:13:08.400
So what do you think. kids?
Beauty. isn't it?

245
00:13:08.400 --> 00:13:11.200
- Wow! Yay. Dad!
- Way to go. Dad!

246
00:13:11.280 --> 00:13:14.920
- Why is there a birdhouse in it?
- Uh. that's an ornament.

247
00:13:15.040 --> 00:13:17.240
Do I smell gunpowder?

248
00:13:17.520 --> 00:13:20.000
and then I want some Robotoids.

249
00:13:20.120 --> 00:13:22.120
And then I want
a Goop Monster.

250
00:13:22.240 --> 00:13:24.040
And then I want
a great big. giant--

251
00:13:24.160 --> 00:13:25.960
Aw. son. you don't need
all that junk.

252
00:13:26.080 --> 00:13:29.040
I'm sure you've already
got something much more important--

253
00:13:29.120 --> 00:13:33.440
a decent home and a loving father
who would do anything for you.

254
00:13:33.560 --> 00:13:36.120
Hey. I couldn't afford lunch.
Give me a bite of that donut.

255
00:13:38.920 --> 00:13:40.840
Get a load of that
quote-unquote Santa.

256
00:13:40.920 --> 00:13:43.040
I can't believe those kids
are falling for it.

257
00:13:43.040 --> 00:13:45.160
Hey. Milhouse. I dare you
to sit on his lap.

258
00:13:45.240 --> 00:13:49.560
- I dare you to yank his beard off.
- Ah. touche.

259
00:13:49.640 --> 00:13:51.480
I hope you feel better.
Santa.

260
00:13:51.560 --> 00:13:53.960
Oh. I will when Mrs. Claus' sisters
get outta town.

261
00:13:53.960 --> 00:13:55.880
Thanks for listenin'. kid.

262
00:13:57.920 --> 00:13:59.720
Hey. Santa.
what's shakin'. man?

263
00:13:59.800 --> 00:14:03.360
What's your name. Bart... ner?
Uh. little partner?

264
00:14:03.480 --> 00:14:06.520
- I'm Bart Simpson. Who are you?
- I'm jolly Old St. Nick.

265
00:14:06.520 --> 00:14:08.920
Oh. yeah?
We'll just see about that.

266
00:14:09.040 --> 00:14:11.520
D'oh!

267
00:14:11.600 --> 00:14:15.240
- Homer!
- A word with you in Santa's workshop.

268
00:14:15.360 --> 00:14:18.520
- Cover for me. Elfie.
- I didn't know it was you.

269
00:14:18.600 --> 00:14:20.520
Nobody knows.
It's a secret.

270
00:14:20.520 --> 00:14:22.440
I didn't get my bonus this year.

271
00:14:22.440 --> 00:14:24.640
But to keep the family
from missing out on Christmas.

272
00:14:24.640 --> 00:14:26.480
- I'd do anything.
- I'll say. Dad.

273
00:14:26.560 --> 00:14:29.640
you must really love us
to sink so low.

274
00:14:31.000 --> 00:14:32.800
Now. let's not get mushy. son.

275
00:14:32.920 --> 00:14:34.840
I still have a job to do.

276
00:14:34.840 --> 00:14:36.760
Hey. little ones. Santa's back.

277
00:14:36.840 --> 00:14:38.760
Ho ho-- D'oh!

278
00:14:38.840 --> 00:14:41.520
Damn it to--

279
00:14:41.640 --> 00:14:43.760
Ah. son. one day
you're gonna know...

280
00:14:43.760 --> 00:14:45.680
the satisfaction of payday.

281
00:14:45.680 --> 00:14:48.920
Receiving a big fat check
for a job well done.

282
00:14:49.000 --> 00:14:50.840
Simpson. Homer?
Here ya go.

283
00:14:50.920 --> 00:14:55.240
Come on. son. Let's go cash
this baby and get presents for--

284
00:14:55.240 --> 00:14:58.040
Thirteen bucks? Hey. wait a minute.

285
00:14:58.120 --> 00:14:59.960
That's right.
$120 gross.

286
00:15:00.040 --> 00:15:01.880
Less Social Security.
less unemployment insurance.

287
00:15:01.960 --> 00:15:03.880
- less Santa training...
- Santa training?

288
00:15:03.880 --> 00:15:05.800
less costume purchase.
less beard rental. less Christmas club.

289
00:15:05.880 --> 00:15:07.920
- But-- But--
- See ya next year.

290
00:15:08.000 --> 00:15:11.000
- Ohh!
- Come on. Dad. Let's go home.

291
00:15:11.000 --> 00:15:12.880
Thirteen bucks?

292
00:15:12.880 --> 00:15:15.120
you can't get anything
for 13 bucks.

293
00:15:15.200 --> 00:15:18.080
Allright!
Thirteen bigones!

294
00:15:18.160 --> 00:15:20.200
Springfield Downs.
here I come!

295
00:15:20.200 --> 00:15:22.400
- What?
- you heard me.

296
00:15:22.480 --> 00:15:24.320
I'm goin' to the dog track.

297
00:15:24.400 --> 00:15:26.320
I got a hot little puppy
in the fourth race.

298
00:15:26.440 --> 00:15:28.320
- Wanna come?
- Sory. Barney.

299
00:15:28.320 --> 00:15:31.520
I may be a total washout as a father.
but I'm not gonna take my kid...

300
00:15:31.600 --> 00:15:33.800
to a sleazy dog track
on Christmas Eve.

301
00:15:33.920 --> 00:15:37.440
Come on. Simpson.
The dog's name is Whirlwind.

302
00:15:37.560 --> 00:15:39.840
Ten-to-one shot.
Money in the bank.

303
00:15:39.840 --> 00:15:41.760
- Uh-uh.
- Ah. come on. Dad.

304
00:15:41.760 --> 00:15:44.560
This can be the miracle that
saves the Simpsons' Christmas.

305
00:15:44.640 --> 00:15:46.480
If TV has taught me anything.

306
00:15:46.560 --> 00:15:49.440
it's that miracles always
happen to poor kids at Christmas.

307
00:15:49.520 --> 00:15:53.080
It happened to Tiny Tim.
it happened to Charlie Brown.

308
00:15:53.160 --> 00:15:55.080
it happened to the Smurfs
and it's gonna happen to us.

309
00:15:56.640 --> 00:16:00.000
Well. okay. let's go.
Who's Tiny Tim?

310
00:16:01.520 --> 00:16:03.440
Hey. Moldy. do you
think Santa will be able to find...

311
00:16:03.440 --> 00:16:05.760
ElfCounty
under all this snow?

312
00:16:05.840 --> 00:16:10.360
I doubt it. Bubbles. We'll be
sad little elves this Christmas.

313
00:16:10.440 --> 00:16:12.280
- Oh. no!
- Oh. brother.

314
00:16:12.360 --> 00:16:14.280
- Where's your husband?
- Yeah. It's getting late.

315
00:16:14.360 --> 00:16:16.880
Said he went caroling
with Bart.

316
00:16:16.960 --> 00:16:20.720
We're in the money.
we're in the money

317
00:16:20.720 --> 00:16:23.880
We got a lot of
what it takes to get along

318
00:16:23.960 --> 00:16:25.960
I can't believe
I'm doing this.

319
00:16:26.080 --> 00:16:28.960
Can we open
our presents now. Dad?

320
00:16:29.040 --> 00:16:31.920
you know the tradition. son.
Not till the eighth race.

321
00:16:32.000 --> 00:16:34.120
Hey. Barney.
which one is Whirlwind?

322
00:16:34.240 --> 00:16:37.960
Number Six. That's our lucky dog
right over there.

323
00:16:38.080 --> 00:16:40.440
He's won
his last five races.

324
00:16:40.440 --> 00:16:42.840
What? That scrawny little
bag of bones?

325
00:16:42.960 --> 00:16:45.440
Come on. Dad. They're all
scrawny little bags of bones.

326
00:16:45.560 --> 00:16:47.840
Yeah. you're right.

327
00:16:47.960 --> 00:16:51.120
I guess Whirlwind is our only hope
for a Merry Christmas.

328
00:16:51.200 --> 00:16:53.400
Attention.
racing fans. we have a late scratch...

329
00:16:53.400 --> 00:16:55.320
in the fourth race.

330
00:16:55.320 --> 00:16:58.280
Number 8. Sir Galahad will be
replaced by Santa's Little Helper.

331
00:16:58.400 --> 00:17:02.240
Once again. Sir Galahad has been
replaced by Santa's Little Helper.

332
00:17:02.320 --> 00:17:04.240
Bart. did you hear that?

333
00:17:04.240 --> 00:17:06.160
What a name!
Santa's Little Helper!

334
00:17:06.240 --> 00:17:09.920
- It's a sign! It's an omen!
- It's a coincidence. Dad.

335
00:17:09.920 --> 00:17:12.880
- What are the odds on Santa's Little
Helper? - Ninety-nine to one.

336
00:17:12.960 --> 00:17:18.360
Wow! Ninety-nine times
thirteen equals... Merry Christmas!

337
00:17:18.440 --> 00:17:20.280
I got a bad feeling
about this.

338
00:17:20.360 --> 00:17:22.160
- Don't you believe in me. son?
- Uh--

339
00:17:22.280 --> 00:17:25.160
Come on. boy. Sometimes your faith
is all that keeps me going.

340
00:17:27.560 --> 00:17:29.960
Oh. go for it. Dad.

341
00:17:30.040 --> 00:17:33.680
That's my boy! Eveything on
Santa's Little Helper.

342
00:17:33.680 --> 00:17:36.000
Three cheers for Brainy!

343
00:17:36.000 --> 00:17:38.480
- Hip hip hooray!
- Yay!

344
00:17:38.560 --> 00:17:40.400
Unadulterated pap.

345
00:17:40.480 --> 00:17:42.880
It's almost 9:00.
Where's Homer anyway?

346
00:17:42.880 --> 00:17:45.760
It's so typical
of the big doof us to spoil it all.

347
00:17:45.760 --> 00:17:47.960
- What. Aunt Patty?
- Oh. nothing. dear.

348
00:17:48.080 --> 00:17:50.000
I'm just trashing
your father.

349
00:17:50.000 --> 00:17:51.920
Well. I wish you wouldn't...

350
00:17:51.920 --> 00:17:56.120
because aside from the fact he has
the same frailties as all human belings.

351
00:17:56.240 --> 00:17:58.040
he's the only father I have.

352
00:17:58.160 --> 00:18:00.720
Therefore. he is
my model of manhood.

353
00:18:00.840 --> 00:18:05.040
and my estimation of him will govern
the prospects of my adult relationships.

354
00:18:05.160 --> 00:18:08.680
So I hope you bear in mind that
any knock at him is a knock at me.

355
00:18:08.680 --> 00:18:12.920
and I'm far too young to defend
myself against such onslaughts.

356
00:18:13.960 --> 00:18:17.040
Mm-hmm. Go watch
your cartoon show. dear.

357
00:18:17.040 --> 00:18:18.960
Come on. Bart.

358
00:18:18.960 --> 00:18:21.640
Kiss the ticket for good luck.
not that we need it.

359
00:18:24.880 --> 00:18:27.120
Here comes
Screwy the mechanical rabbit.

360
00:18:27.120 --> 00:18:28.640
- and they're off!

361
00:18:28.720 --> 00:18:31.800
- Come on. Santa's Little Helper!
- Come on. dog! Go. man. go!

362
00:18:31.800 --> 00:18:34.880
It's Whirlwind in the lane. and
coming up on the left is Quadruped.

363
00:18:34.960 --> 00:18:37.000
followed by Dog O'War
and Fido.

364
00:18:37.080 --> 00:18:39.960
- Go! Come on. boy!
- Go! Come on. get that rabbit!

365
00:18:40.040 --> 00:18:42.440
Dog O'War coming up fast
on the outside.

366
00:18:42.560 --> 00:18:44.480
- Come on. Santa's Little Helper!
- Come on. dog! Go. man. go!

367
00:18:44.560 --> 00:18:47.640
And with a lock on last place.
it's Santa's Little Helper.

368
00:18:47.720 --> 00:18:51.280
- Don't worry. Dad.

369
00:18:51.360 --> 00:18:54.440
Maybe this is just for suspense
before the miracle happens.

370
00:18:54.520 --> 00:18:57.800
- Come on. you stupid dog! Come on!
- Go. go!

371
00:18:57.880 --> 00:19:00.000
- Run! Run!
- Run. run! Come on. get that rabbit!

372
00:19:00.080 --> 00:19:02.680
- Go. go. Santa's Little Helper! Run!
- Go. go. go!

373
00:19:02.800 --> 00:19:06.800
Whirlwind by a countrymile. second.
ChewMyShoe. followed by Dog O'War.

374
00:19:06.920 --> 00:19:09.200
Oh. jeez!

375
00:19:09.200 --> 00:19:12.480
Doesn't seem possible.
but I guess TV has betrayed me.

376
00:19:12.480 --> 00:19:14.960
I don't wanna leave
till our dog finishes.

377
00:19:19.960 --> 00:19:21.760
Ah. forget it.
Let's go.

378
00:19:30.600 --> 00:19:33.200
- Find any winners. son?
- Sory. Dad.

379
00:19:33.280 --> 00:19:36.160
Hey. hey. Simpson!
What'dl tell you?

380
00:19:36.160 --> 00:19:39.320
Whirlwind!
Let's go. Daria.

381
00:19:43.840 --> 00:19:46.880
Beat it! Scram! Get lost!

382
00:19:47.000 --> 00:19:49.600
- you came in last for the last time!

383
00:19:49.680 --> 00:19:51.880
Look. Dad. it's
Santa's Little Helper.

384
00:19:52.000 --> 00:19:54.760
And don't come back!

385
00:19:54.760 --> 00:19:57.240
Oh. no. you don't! No. no!
Get away from me! Uh-uh!

386
00:20:00.320 --> 00:20:02.800
Oh. can we keep him.
Dad. please?

387
00:20:02.920 --> 00:20:06.080
But he's a loser!
He's pathetic! He's--

388
00:20:08.080 --> 00:20:10.000
A Simpson.

389
00:20:13.000 --> 00:20:15.480
Hmm. Maybe I should
call the police.

390
00:20:15.560 --> 00:20:18.640
- Oh. he'll sober up.
- Yeah. Come staggering home.

391
00:20:18.640 --> 00:20:20.840
Mm-hmm.
Smelling of cheap perfume.

392
00:20:20.840 --> 00:20:22.960
- Homer!

393
00:20:23.040 --> 00:20:25.560
- What? What the-- Who the--
- Look. eveybody.

394
00:20:25.640 --> 00:20:29.080
